Activity - 7

Is an array that is sorted in Ascending order a min-oriented heap? Why?

Yes, it is a min-oriented heap.

For, Example:-

a = [5, 6, 7, 8, 9]

						    5
						   /\
						  /  \
						 6	  7
						/\
					   8  9

The root is smaller than the child in every level and it does not take any exchanges.